Kuwait, an oil-rich city-state, has 1. Early Friday, the invaders controlled Kuwait city, the capital. President Bush denounced it as naked agression. CAUSE OF CONFLICT: President Saddam Hussein of Iraq accused Kuwait of stealing oil from its territory and forcing down oil prices through overproduction. A Pentagon source said a US naval group was diverted toward the Persian Gulf. Diplomatic sources estimate more than 200 Kuwaitis were killed or wounded, mainly from the Emiri Guard which bore the main brunt of the invasion. Kuwait's Sheik Saad al-Abdullah al-Sabah fled to safety in Saudi Arabia. 